alerts.headline: Coastal Flood Watch issued February 20 at 12:24PM EST until February 24 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Boston/Norton MA
alerts.description:
* WHAT...Minor to moderate coastal flooding possible. Flooding
could be as deep as 1 to 3 feet.

* WHERE...Eastern Massachusetts coast, including Cape Cod and the
Islands.

* WHEN...From Monday evening through Tuesday morning.

* IMPACTS...Numerous roads may be closed around high tides early
Monday morning and again early Tuesday morning. Debris may wash
onto coastal roads from wave action. Low lying property
including homes, businesses, and some critical infrastructure
may be inundated. Significant beach erosion is likely.

alerts.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 20 at 12:15PM EST until February 21 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Boston/Norton MA
alerts.description:
* WHAT...Mixed precipitation. Additional snow accumulations between
2 and 4 inches and ice accumulations around a light glaze.

* WHERE...Portions of central, eastern, northeastern, and western
Massachusetts.

* WHEN...Until 7 AM EST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the Friday evening commute.
